Phase II: User Requirements and Application Specifications
Project: Smart Library Management System

#1 Chosen Development Model

Agile Development Model

Justification:
The Agile model was the selected model, because it allows flexibility and continuous improvement during development. 
The project contains different sections like book borrowing, e-books, and student notes. From that, Agile makes it easier to develop features step by step, test them, and improve them based on feedback given by users.

#2. User Requirements

a. Stakeholders:

1. Students
- Borrow physical books
- Access e-books
- Upload and download notes
- Track borrowed books and deadlines

2. Librarians
- Manage books
- Approve borrowing requests
- Track returns

3. Admin
- Manage users
- Manage e-books and notes
- Monitor the whole system

4. Developers
- Build and maintain the system

5. Guest User
Roles:
- Can browse into limited content without logging in

6. University Administrator
Roles:
- Monitor academic systems and performance

7. Content Reviewer
Roles:
- Reviews and validates uploaded notes

8. Lecturer
Roles:
- Provides academic content and guidance

9. IT Support Staff
Roles:
- Maintains system functionality

10. External E-Book Provider 
Roles:
- Provides additional E-books

b. User Stories
- As a student, I want to search books by title or author, so I can quickly find what I need.

- As a student, I want to see the return date of borrowed books to avoid late returns.

- As a student, I want to borrow e-books online, so I can access materials from anywhere.

- As a student, I want to upload study notes, so I can help other students.

- As an admin, I want to add and remove books to keep the database updated.

- As a librarian, I want to track borrowed books, to know which books are available.

- As a developer, I want to build and maintain the system using codes, so the app is easier to update and improve.

- As a guest user, I want to browse available books and notes, so I can decide to register in the system.

- As an university administrator, I want to view reports related to system usage, so I can evaluate how effectively students are using library materials.

- As a content reviewer, I want to review and approve student notes, so materials uploaded on the app are accurate and high-quality level.

- As an IT support staff, I want to monitor system errors to fix technical problems quickly.

- As a lecturer, I want to upload accurate materials and notes to help students to better understand course topics.

- As an external e-book provider, I want to integrate my digital library with system, so students can access more online resources.

#3. Functional Requirements

1. User Registration and Login
Description:
The system should allow users to create an account and log in.

Acceptance Criteria:
- User enters email and password
- System verifies credentials
- User is redirected to dashboard
- Error message appears for invalid login

2. Search Books
Description:
The system should allow users to search books by title, author, or category.

Acceptance Criteria:
- User enters a search term
- System displays matching books
- Results show availability status

3. Borrow Physical Books
Description:
The system should allow students to borrow books.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Student selects a book
- System checks availability
- Borrow date and return date are recorded
