#5. Application Specifications

a. Architecture
The system follows a three-tier architecture that includes a frontend that provides user interface for students, librarians, and admins. 
The other part of the system is backend that  handles business logic, authentication, and borrowing operations and the last part is the database.
The database stores users, books, borrowings, e-books, and notes.

b. Database Model
The database includes tables that are users, books, borrowings, Ebooks, notes. 
In these tables one user can borrow many books, while one book can have many borrow records. 
Also, one user can upload many notes.

c. Technologies Used
The system is developed using HTML, CSS and JavaScript for the frontend development, because these programming languages are easier and flexible to implement.
For the backend development, used language is the Python due to its simplicity. 
The database uses MySQL for the efficient data management and simple manipulations in the database. 

d. User Interface Design
The system includes a login, dashboard, search books , borrowed books, E-book library and a student notes page. 
The interface is simple, clear and easy understandable for the users of the system. 

e. Security Measures
The system uses an user authentication with secured login credentials like email and password. 
The passwords are encrypted before storage. 
Also the database has a protected access that allows only authorized part of development team to have access on the database of the system.

